      <body>
         <head><title>Poem 6 (J 281: 1861/1935)</title></head>
         <lg>
            <l>'Tis so appalling&#8212;it exhilarates&#8212;</l>
            <l>So over Horror,
               <app>
                  <rdg wit="var0 #fh #df16">it half Captivates&#8212;</rdg>
                  <rdg wit="var1 #df16">it dumb fascinates&#8212;</rdg>
               </app>
            </l>
            <l>The Soul stares after it, secure&#8212;</l>
            <l>
               <app>
                  <rdg wit="var0 #df16">To know the worst, leaves no dread more&#8212;</rdg>
                  <rdg wit="var1 #fh #df16">A Sepulchre, fears frost, no more&#8212;</rdg>
               </app>
            </l>
         </lg>
         <lg>
            <l>To scan a Ghost, is faint&#8212;</l>
            <l><app>
               <rdg wit="#df16">But grappling, Conquers it&#8212;</rdg>
               <rdg wit="#fh">But grappling, conquers it&#8212;</rdg>
            </app></l>
            <l><app>
               <rdg wit="#df16">How Easy Torment, now&#8212;</rdg>
               <rdg wit="#fh">How easy, Torment, now&#8212;</rdg>
            </app></l>
            <l>Suspense kept sawing so&#8212;</l>
         </lg>
         <lg>
            <l>The Truth, is Bald, and Cold&#8212;</l>
            <l>But that will hold&#8212;</l>
            <l>If any are not sure&#8212;</l>
            <l>We show them&#8212;prayer&#8212;</l>
            <l>But we, who know,</l>
            <l>Stop hoping, now&#8212;</l>
         </lg>
         <lg>
            <l>Looking at Death, is Dying&#8212;</l>
            <l>Just let go the Breath&#8212;</l>
            <l>And not the pillow at your Cheek</l>
            <l>So Slumbereth&#8212;</l>
         </lg>
         <lg>
            <l>Others, Can wrestle&#8212;</l>
            <l>Yours, is done&#8212;</l>
            <l>And so of Woe, bleak dreaded&#8212;come,</l>
            <l>It sets the Fright at liberty&#8212;</l>
            <l>And Terror's free&#8212;</l>
            <l>Gay, Ghastly, Holiday!</l>
         </lg>
